AS INTRODUCED
6
7
An Act relating to county libraries; authorizing
7
certain counties to reduce millage rate of special
8
levy; prescribing information requirements for
8
resolution to reduce levy; providing for
9
codification; and providing an effective date.
9
10
10
11
11
12
BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
12
13
SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
13
14
in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 170 of Title 65, unless there is
14
15
created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
15
16
A. For any county that funds a county library or metropolitan
16
17
library by a special levy approved by the voters pursuant to Section
17
18
10A of Article X of the Oklahoma Constitution, the board of county
18
19
commissioners may reduce such levy by resolution. Provided, the
19
20
reduced special levy shall not be less than the minimum of one (1)
20
21
mill, as required pursuant to Section 10A of Article X of the
21
22
Oklahoma Constitution.
22
23
23
24
24
